#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:64
msgid "We use this information to communicate with Other volunteers, including communication about the organisation and opportunities to volunteer. Additionally, we may use volunteer information to contact you about additional opt-in opportunities for assessment, training, teaching, volunteering and/or community engagement. This information may also be used for statistical purposes. We do not provide personally identifiable information to any third party. However, we may share de-identified aggregate or summary information regarding volunteers publicly or with other volunteers, partners or third parties, including but not limited to funding entities.\n"
"See [Section 6: All Participants](#section-6-all-participants) for further information."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:67
# header
msgid "## Section 4: Online Spaces"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:68
msgid "This Privacy Policy is applicable to information that you provided/collected through physical (such as a paper form) and online means, including through our websites or other external online spaces (including but not limited to GitHub repositories, Etherpads, Google Documents, EventBrite and mailing lists). By using these spaces, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy. Some of these tools and services (including but not limited to GitHub, Google Documents, Eventbrite and SurveyMonkey) have their own independent privacy policies. See [Section 5: Opt-In Surveys](#section-5-opt-in-surveys), for information specifically on survey information."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:71
msgid "We may collect information about visitors’ devices and browsers, such as browser version and type, IP address, website referred from and country of visitor.\n"
"In addition, we may collect textual input (e.g. Etherpad entries) from you which may be associated with your name, affiliation and/or social media handles.\n"
"If you provide financial information to pay for a workshop or partnership or make a donation, the transaction information will be processed on a third-party secured site. This information will only be accessible to our Core Team or authorised administrators and to the Core Team of our fiscal sponsor who is involved in processing financial transactions. We engage with third-parties (including but not limited to Square, WeDidIt, Eventbrite) to gather and collect this information securely and do not have access to or store any payment details in our systems."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:75
#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:86
# header
msgid "#### What do we do with this information?"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:76
msgid "We use this information to improve our sites and services. In addition, we may use contact information that you provide to contact you about additional opt-in opportunities for assessment, training, teaching, and/or community engagement. This information may also be used for statistical purposes. We do not provide personally identifiable information to any third party. However, we may share de-identified aggregate or summary information regarding visitors publicly or with volunteers, partners or third parties, including but not limited to funding entities. We may use publicly available data of the external online services in programmatic analysis and evaluation.\n"
"See [Section 6: All Participants](#section-6-all-participants) for further information."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:79
# header
msgid "## Section 5: Opt-in Surveys"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:80
msgid "Community and workshop participants are invited to participate in a variety of opt-in surveys to better serve our community. These include but are not limited to pre-workshop and post-workshop surveys of learners and various survey instruments to evaluate programs or events. "
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:83
msgid "Opt-in surveys are entirely voluntary and information is not collected in a way that it is linked to personally identifiable responses without the respondent’s consent to self-identify.\n"
"Surveys collect information particular to the event or program being evaluated and optional information about the participant. Gender and ethnicity data, when collected, is only collected from participants in the United States."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:87
msgid "We use this information to help evaluate and improve programs, report on impact and outcomes and understand the needs and interests of our community. This information may be used for statistical purposes. We do not provide personally identifiable information to any third party. However, we may share de-identified aggregate or summary information publicly or with volunteers, partners or third parties, including but not limited to funding entities. Where we share open-ended responses or testimonials, we always do so anonymously or ask for explicit consent to allow de-identified responses.\n"
"See [Section 6: All Participants](#section-6-all-participants) for further information."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:90
# header
msgid "## Section 6: All Participants"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:92
# header
msgid "#### Can I decide what communications to receive?"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:93
msgid "Yes. All communication with us is opt-in, except for participants receiving information about their program and for instructors, information required to maintain instructor status. You may occasionally be sent emails asking if you would like to opt-in to communication channels that we feel may be of interest to you (for example, a mailing list dedicated to your geographical area). In the absence of specific action from you, we will assume you choose not to join these channels."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:95
# header
msgid "#### Removing personal information"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:96
msgid "Participants may choose to disallow us from retaining their personal information at any time by notifying [admin@carpentries.org](mailto:admin@carpentries.org). If you choose to exclude your information, we will delete your personal information from our databases. This may interfere with our ability to give you credit for training events you have completed or to contact you about upcoming events in your area."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:98
# header
msgid "#### Limitations"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:99
msgid "Your privacy is very important to us. However, due to the existing legal and technical environment (e.g., third party interception of information), we cannot ensure that your personally identifiable information will not be disclosed to third parties in ways not described in this policy.\n"
"We may disclose information when we believe such disclosure is necessary to comply with the law; enforce our agreements, or protect the rights, property or safety of our users or others."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:102
# header
msgid "#### What about third party links on our websites?"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:103
msgid "Our websites provide links to third party sites as a service to visitors. We are not responsible for the privacy practices, security measures or data collection practices of third party sites or for their content. The choice to access these sites is at the visitor’s own risk."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:105
# header
msgid "#### Who should be contacted regarding this Privacy Policy?"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/privacy.md:106
msgid "For questions or comments about this Privacy Policy, please contact [admin@carpentries.org](mailto:admin@carpentries.org)."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:1
# header
msgid "### Code of Conduct Termed Suspension Guidelines"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:3
# header
msgid "##### The Carpentries Termed Suspension Checklist"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:5
msgid "As a part of their enforcement options, The Carpentries Code of Conduct (CoC) committee can place a community member in Termed Suspension, where the community member is removed from all Carpentries engagement for a period of time."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:7
msgid "The goal of a Termed Suspension is to 1) limit a person's participation in virtual and in-person Carpentries spaces for a set time to create a safe space for the community, and 2) to give time and opportunity for the individual to review their response to the incident and demonstrate immediate, ongoing, and demonstrable changes as evaluated by the CoC committee before possible reinstatement."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:9
msgid "In most cases, a Termed Suspension will only be enacted after an incident has been reviewed by the CoC committee and a resolution is reached. However, in severe situations, in particular where there is active harassment, the CoC committee may enact an immediate short-term Termed Suspension while an incident is under review."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:11
msgid "If there is a decision for a Termed Suspension, the following checklist is followed by the appropriate personnel to enact the Termed Suspension. In accordance with CoC confidentiality guidelines, only essential personnel will be involved in implementation of these actions."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:13
# header
msgid "##### Online Communication and Communities"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:14
msgid "Revoke access from the following communication channels and communities: \n"
"- Email lists on [TopicBox](https://carpentries.topicbox.com/groups) \n"
"- Email lists on Google Groups including but not limited to:\n"
"  - Library Carpentry Governance Group\n"
"  - Library Carpentry Maintainer Onboarding\n"
"  - Code of Conduct Committee\n"
"  - Carpentries Mentoring Groups \n"
"- Twitter:\n"
"    - [@datacarpentry](https://twitter.com/datacarpentry)\n"
"    - [@swcarpentry](https://twitter.com/swcarpentry)\n"
"    - [@libcarpentry](https://twitter.com/libcarpentry)\n"
"    - [@thecarpentries](https://twitter.com/thecarpentries)\n"
"- Blogs\n"
"    - [Data Carpentry](https://datacarpentry.org/blog/)\n"
"    - [Software Carpentry](https://software-carpentry.org/blog/)\n"
"    - [Library Carpentry](https://librarycarpentry.org/blog/)\n"
"    - [The Carpentries](https://carpentries.org/blog/)\n"
"- GitHub (including but not limited to carpentries, datacarpentry, swcarpentry, librarycarpentry, data-lessons, carpentrieslab)\n"
"- Gitter - Library Carpentry Lobby\n"
"- [Slack](https://swcarpentry.slack.com/messages)  \n"
"- [Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/carpentries/) \n"
"- [LinkedIn Carpentries](https://www.linkedin.com/company/the-carpentries/about/) and [LinkedIn Instructors](https://www.linkedin.com/groups/8279689/)"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:37
msgid "Additionally, the community member will not be allowed to attend community discussions."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:39
# header
msgid "##### Teaching Workshops"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:40
msgid "The suspended member will, for the duration of their suspension:\n"
"- Be asked not to sign up for workshops on the Instructor Spreadsheet.\n"
"- Not be able to participate as a helper at any workshops.\n"
"- Be removed from Eventbrite login access.\n"
"- Not be allowed to plan self-organised workshops.\n"
"- Not be allowed to request or host centrally coordinated workshops.\n"
"- Not be listed as an instructor on the “Instructors” webpage.\n"
"- Be removed from the instructors email list."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:49
# header
msgid "##### Organising Workshops "
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:50
msgid "If the suspended member is a Regional Coordinator or serves in another role whereby they organise workshops for The Carpentries, for the duration of their suspension they will not have access to:\n"
"- LastPass\n"
"- AMY\n"
"- Regional Email\n"
"- Asana\n"
"- HelpScout\n"
"- Zoom\n"
"- Regional Coordinators Slack Channel\n"
"- Regional Coordinators Email List"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:60
# header
msgid "##### Instructor Training"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:61
msgid "The suspended member will, for the duration of their suspension, be removed from the “Our Trainers” web page. Additionally, the suspended member will not be allowed to: \n"
"- Teach Instructor Training or lead teaching demonstration sessions. The Deputy Director of Instructor Training (DDIT) will check the teaching demo Etherpad to ensure that the suspended member is not signed up to lead teaching demonstrations and will find a replacement Trainer as needed. \n"
"- Join Trainer meetings. The DDIT will check the meeting Etherpad, and if the suspended member is signed up to attend, will email them if needed to confirm they will not be in attendance. \n"
"- Post pull requests (PRs), issues, or comments to the Instructor Training GitHub repository. Write or administrative access to repositories will be removed for the duration of the suspension. \n"
"- Post to the Trainers Slack channel or mailing lists. The suspended member will be removed from these lists for the duration of their suspension. \n"
"- Participate in review of applications for open instructor training or Trainer training. \n"
"Participate as a learner in instructor training."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:69
# header
msgid "##### Trainer Training"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:70
msgid "The suspended member will not be allowed to participate in Trainer Training (if they are currently enrolled) and will not be accepted for Trainer Training (if they apply during the suspension period). Additionally, they will not be allowed to shadow a current Carpentries Trainer. They may apply or reapply for future rounds of Trainer Training. "
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:72
# header
msgid "##### Member Organisation and Local Activities"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:73
msgid "The suspended member shall not be involved in officially branded Carpentries workshops or activities at the member or local site for the duration of the suspension. We expect the suspended member to assert that they will be able to carry out this suspension accordingly and to notify the CoC committee if this suspension will interfere with their expected employment duties. "
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:75
msgid "If the suspension does affect employment duties or the suspended member is the key contact for a member site, the member will work with The Carpentries Executive Director to determine a course of action."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:77
# header
msgid "##### Lesson Development and Maintenance"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:78
msgid "The suspended member will not be allowed to post PRs, issues, or comments to any repository in the carpentries, including but not limited to datacarpentry, swcarpentry, library carpentry, data-lessons, and carpentrieslab organisations. Administrative or write privileges to repositories in these organisations will be removed for the duration of the suspension."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:80
msgid "If the suspended member is a Maintainer, their name will be removed from the lessons page and they will not appear on the Maintainers page for the duration of their suspension. "
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:82
# header
msgid "##### Executive Council"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:83
msgid "If the suspended member is a member of the Executive Council, they will not participate in Executive Council responsibilities and will be removed from the Executive Council repositories and list of Executive Council members on the website for the duration of their suspension. The Executive Council will review the CoC incident to determine if a suspension will affect their long term position on the Executive Council."
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:85
# header
msgid "##### Committees, Task Forces, and Other Interactions"
msgstr ""

#: topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:86
msgid "Involvement in all committees, communities, and task forces (African Task Force, Carpentries en LatinoAmérica, etc.) will be suspended. "
